>So he would wake up in the morning and trade Treasury futures and options:=
</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Leech typically began trading =
around 5 a.m. Pacific Time (=E2=80=9CPT=E2=80=9D) (i.e., 8 a.m. Eastern Tim=
e (=E2=80=9CET=E2=80=9D)), and traded all day, generally placing dozens of =
trades per day.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">He would do th=
ese trades in an omnibus account, which =E2=80=9Callows an investment advis=
