=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One theory that you sometimes hear about Renaissance T=
echnologies is that it employs very smart researchers to come up with tradi=
ng strategies, but its real advantage is in data. Renaissance has had a lon=
g time to accumulate and analyze and carefully scrub a lot of data sources,=
 so if you want to build a quantitative trading strategy at Renaissance, yo=
u can use sophisticated machine-learning techniques to extract signals from=
 that data, and those signals will work. But if you were to quit Renaissanc=
e and go out on your own, you might be just as smart and just as good at ma=
chine learning, but your data won=E2=80=99t be as good, so your signals won=
=E2=80=99t work. You will apply your sophisticated techniques to not-quite-=
right or not-quite-complete data, and they will generate incorrect answers.=
 Conversely, Renaissance can hire smart scientists, computational linguists=
, etc., who are good at machine-learning techniques but know nothing about =
finance, because it can give them pristine financial=C2=A0data and let them=
 get to work.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could extrapolate a model=
 from this in which a quantitative hedge fund does three essential things:<=
/p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px =
0;"> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It acquires and scrubs financial and=
 financial-adjacent data.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It employs=
 researchers who=C2=A0analyze=C2=A0that data to find signals that predict f=
inancial returns.</li> <li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It implements thos=
e signals by trading securities.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Step=
s 1 and 3 are essential financial functions that the fund does as an instit=
ution, and that its researchers couldn=E2=80=99t do on their own. Step 2 is=
 sort of pure scientific research, which relies on the curiosity and creati=
vity and whimsy of the researchers. The researchers are generally paid pret=
ty well and signed to strict nondisclosure agreements, but you could imagin=
e a different model. There are a lot of curious, creative, whimsical, numer=
ate people interested in scientific research, and money. You have the data =
and the trading, which are hard to replicate; could you just outsource the =
research=3F</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Justina Lee=
